her persons to be selected by them,\niree to be representative of labor, three\ncapital and three to represent the gen- 1\nal public. The income from the founda- on\nfund is to be paid by the trustees to j\nlis committee of sixteen, which shaJl ar- j\ninge for conferences in this city of la-\nar and capital, \"for the purpose of dis- j\njssing industrial problems with the view I\nf arriving at a better understanding beveen\nemployers and employes.\" It is\niade mandatory upcn the industrial\n?ace committee to call such conferences\ni case of great industrial crises and to\nike such other steps as in its discretion\nill promote the general purposes of the\nlundation.\nOCEAN LINER MOVEMENTS.\nNEW YORK, March 21.?Arrived:\nteamer Regina d'ltalia, Genoa and\naples.\nSailed: Steamers Furnessia, Glasgow;\nraf Waldersee, Hamburg; I.usitania,\niverpool via Queenstown; Minnehaha,\n-ondon; New York, ^Southampton via\nlymoutli and Cherbourg; Perugia,\naples; Vaderland, Antwerp via Dover.\nHAVRE, March 21.?Sailed: Steamer\na Gascogne, New York.\nQUEENSTOWN. March 20.?Arrived:\nteamer Marion for Philadelphia and\nroeeeded. i\nBRISBANE, March 21.?Arrived preiously:\nSteamer Aorangia, Vancouver\nia Honolulu for Sydney.\nHONG KONG. March 21.?Arrived preiously:\nSteamer Bellerophon, Tacoma\nud Seattle via Yokohama for Liverpool.\nLIVERPOOL, March 21.?Arrived:\nteamer Sylvania. Boston.\nST. VINCENT, C. V., March 21.-Sailed:\nteamer Craigvar (from Portland, Ore., 1\nia Coronel), Antwerp. I\nMANCHESTER. March 20.?Sailed:\nteamer Bcstonian, Boston.\nANTWERP. March 21.?Sailed: Steamer\niroonland. New York via Dover.\nSOUTHAMPTON. March 21.?Sailed: j\nteamer Philadfe'.phla, New York via\nneruouifi.\nPLYMOUTH. March -1. Arrived:\nteamer St. Paul New York for Cheraurg\nand Southampton, and proceeded.\nLIBAU. March ltJ.?Sailed: Steamer\netersburg, New York via Rotterdam.\nPALERMO. March 21.?Sailed: Steamer\nrancesoa, from Trieste. New York.\nST. VINCENT. C. V., March lb?Sailed: 1\nteamer Hut