ryan, waa\nelected one of the delegates, and will undoubtedly\nsucceed himself on the national\ncommittee. After the convention the\nBryan men expressed themselves as perfectly\nsatisfied with the results.\nTHE STAR TODAY.\nThe Star today consists of seven parts,\nas follows:\nPages\nPart 1?News 20\nPart II?Editorial 8\nPart III?Magazine 30\nPart IV?Special features 8\nPart V?Sports 4\nPart VI?Comic Section 4\nPart VII?Women's Section 12\nPart On.. p,?\nRaise for Clerks Killed in Senate 1\nStrong for Cannon 1\nDoubts Taft Total 1\nMessage This Week 1\nlows Honors Hughes 2\nfortifications Bill 2\nSeta Theta PI Dinner 2\nDarter Beats Uncle Sam 8\nEVorkingmen's Pensions 3\nSo Itaids at Benning 5\nAdditions to the Zoo 5\nrhe Foreign Stage 7\nfelons Work Slowly 8\nVrrny and Navy News 8\nVround the City 10\nBlack Belt Orderly 12\nGrecian Minister an Accomplished Diplomat. 12\nEVelfare of the City 13\nCapital's King Baker 13\nS'oted Washington Builder 17\nSigns of Prosperity 17\n'\"ibaucial Page lU\nPart Two. Pl?.\nis the Cartoonists See tbe Neva 2\njotA Caminarleigb's Secret 2\nMusical Mention..., 3\nxmdon Letter 3\nEditorials 4\nin tbe Kealm of Higher Things S\nL'be Theater 6\nflayers' Paragraphs 7\njOcal News 8\nPart Threa. p#fie\nTHE DIVA'S RUBY. BY F. MARION\nCRAWFORD i 6\nBeing Broke. By Clarence L. Collen 3\nThe Wisdom of Sri Ganesh. By Flora Anule\nSteel 7\nA Father's Blessing. By Charles Belmont\nDavis 9\nPatting in One for Hiram. By Sewell Ford. 11\n\"The .Most Useful Cltiren.\" By John Hubert\nGreusel 13\nMarvels of Ship Surgery. By W. G. FltzGeraid\n17\nFeminization of Boys. By Alexander T.\nStuart... 19\nPart Four. p,fe\nHistory of a Square 1\nWhen Spring Comes at the Zoo 2\nAnecdotes of Well-known People 2\nDomestic Science for the Mothers of tbe\nFuture 3\nThe Hotel Clerk's Tale 3\nSafety of Traveling Women in Metropolitan\nHotels 3\nAssumes the Role of Seer in Russia 4\nThe Fountain of Youth 4\nFeathered Immigrants That Come <o the\nStates 5\nTo Make Easy t